    <p>
			Workshop participants engage in a rigorous daily schedule where they participate in <b>over 5 hours of class and practice</b>.  In addition to training, students are responsible for maintaining their personal environment by taking care of the Gurukula, cleaning their own living spaces, doing their laundry and cleaning up after each meal. 
		</p>
    <p>
			Even though the workshop offers basic training in Odissi, in true Nrityagram fashion students are also taught Yoga and physical conditioning techniques based on traditional exercises and the Natyashastra.  The study of dance-scriptures like the Abhinaya Darpana is an integral part of the experience, in addition to learning rhythmic exercises based on structures specific to Odissi dance. 
		</p>
